  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0d9a \u0d85\u0d82\u0dc1 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The President meets the security chiefs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe as the Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces today (July 21) visited the Ministry of Defense at the Defense Headquarters Complex in Sri Jayawardenepura Kotte after taking oath in Parliament.",
        "The President was received by Defense Secretary General Kamal Gunaratne who came to the Defense Ministry.",
        "After being sworn in as the President, Mr. Wickramasinghe first visited a government institution, where he met with the heads of the security forces and held a discussion.",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe was sworn in as the 8th Executive President of Sri Lanka this morning in Parliament.",
        "Minister Tiral Alas, Attorney General, Secretary to the President, Chief of Defense Staff, Commanders of the three armed forces, Inspector General of Police, Chief of National Intelligence, Director of State Intelligence Service and senior officers of the Ministry were present on this occasion."
      ],
